v 0.1.1:

 * Fix bug affecting all 32-bit systems.
 * Fix bug affecting Ubuntu 12.04.
 * Add `save` builtin for error handling.
 * Make distribution more complete.
 * The spec is in the distribution. It is fairly close to the implementation.
 * Allow imports from FFFLL_DIR environment variable.
 * Imports are now contained entirely in their own namespace.

v 0.1:

 * Finally got around to autotools! Yay!
 * The language is fairly complete. Look at the spec!
 * Stuff is dynamically allocated and reference countd.
 * Most stuff is free()'d before exit.
 * In any case, no memory leaks!
